## How Manual Final Persistence Works Right Now
Persistence uses `AuditLog`, not a new Prisma model.

### Pending manual final batch
- `action = MANUAL_FINAL_LABEL_PENDING`
- `entity = FINAL_ASSEMBLY_LABEL`

### Confirmed/saved manual final batch
- `action = MANUAL_FINAL_LABEL_PRINT`
- `entity = FINAL_ASSEMBLY_LABEL`

### Stored payload in `AuditLog.details`
JSON includes:
- `stage`
- `productCode`
- `productName`
- `prefix`
- `partyName`
- `partyCode`
- `clientId`
- `items` (`serial`, `copies`)
- `totalStickers`
- `source`
- `status`
- `generatedAt`
- `confirmedAt`

## Current Manual Final Flow in Code (local HEAD `168bee3`)

### Page load
`app/print/unit/manual/page.tsx`
- loads active clients
- loads audit logs for:
  - `MANUAL_FINAL_LABEL_PENDING`
  - `MANUAL_FINAL_LABEL_PRINT`
- maps them into:
  - `initialPending`
  - `initialHistory`

### Generate
`app/print/unit/manual/ManualFinalLabel.tsx`
- validates prefix and party
- POSTs to `/api/print/unit/manual`
- creates a pending batch only
- prints the stickers
- shows confirmation UI

### Save barcode / confirm print
`app/print/unit/manual/ManualFinalLabel.tsx`
- PATCHes `/api/print/unit/manual` with selected `batchIds`
- moves those batches from pending to history

### Reprint
`app/print/unit/manual/ManualFinalLabel.tsx`
- rebuilds sticker data from a pending batch
- prints again
- keeps the batch pending until user explicitly saves it

